title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer 556R AK Sniper 7.62x39 Laser & Scope         AK-47 AR-15 M4 style Not Colt M&P BushMaster AR10
postcontent:
Folks, here is your chance to own an accurate AK system, "Assault Rifle", that is American made.  The Sig Sauer 556R, 7.62 x 39, is as reliable as Russian's AK-47 but is much more accurate at 100-200 yards.  Sig Sauer's 556R is based on a combined technology of a dependable AK, coupled with the ease and MilSpec, upper/lower concept, similar of a U.S. AR-15 M4 system.  It is the combination of the these two exceptional features that allowed the Sig Sauer 556R to deliver the deadly 7.62 x 39 rounds with the accurate comparable to an AR-15. title: For Sale:  Lee Pro 1000 45 ACP PROGRESSIVE PRESS *NEW* WILL SET UP FOR YOU *READ DESCRIPTION*
postcontent:
This press in brand new in the box. Also included is a new case collator (see pictures) that will turn all of the brass right side up when dropping into the feeding tubes. You need nothing else to start reloading 45 ACP!!!  I have been reloading with Lee presses for over 30 years. In my opinion they are the best reloaders on the market, and when you bring in the price it is hands down. The Lee pro 1000 is an un-real press; I currently own 3 and switch out calibers on all of them, doing almost 12 calibers on these presses. I attached a some pictures of one of my reloading setups just to show my experience with the presses and possibly some ideas on how to set yours up (these are the last pictures). The Lee pro 1000 will come with literally everything you need to start reloading 45 ACP; all you will need is brass, bullets, primers, and powders. With the price of .45 ACP ammo going through the roof with no stop in sight, this is a great way to save money and assure yourself you will always have ammunition. Also keep in mind this press will do all other pistol calibers, all you need to do is get the 3 die set for which ever caliber you desire. I also have these just message me on which caliber you would like. Switching from one caliber to another is very easy with this press, taking 5 minutes or less!

What I have chosen to do for my customers that will make this the easy press setup possible is to tune all of the dies so the press is literally ready to go right out of the box. I take the the turret (the turret is what holds the three dies) and the 3 dies out of the box and put on one of my presses and set all of the dies EXACTLY to where they should be set. This is by far the most important factor in getting this press working great and reloading top quality ammunition. So when you get this press installed it is literally ready to start reloading and you don’t have to deal with the hassle of setting up each die which can be challenging for a first time reloader or even an experienced one. I have chosen to do this just because I feel like it makes the whole process of getting into reloading that much easier, IF FOR WHATEVER REASON YOU DO NOT WANT ME TO GO AHEAD AND SET YOUR DIES UP JUST LET ME KNOW IN A MESSAGE AND I WILL NOT MESS WITH THEM AT ALL!!

My experience with Lee customer service has been a truly great experience from day one; they have  some of the best customer service representatives and are VERY knowledgeable especially on the Lee Pro 1000. If you ever have any types of problems or just have general reloading questions you can always get through to a representative at Lee, unlike many other companies you may be on hold for an hour. Also they have great how to videos on their website, they are short clips that show you how to do everything imaginable on this Lee Pro 1000 from changing calibers, setting up dies, cleaning the press, changing the shellplate (if desired), literally everything. I WILL ALSO BE HAPPY TO HELP AS I FEEL I AM AS KNOWLEDGABLE ON THESE PRESSES THAN ANYONE ELSE, THEY ARE MY PASSION, I SERIOUSLY LOVE THEM!!

THESE PRESSES ARE NOT "FACTORY RECONDITIONED" LIKE OTHERS ON HERE. EVERYTHING IS BRAND NEW IN BOX WITH A 2 YEAR WARRANTY NO QUESTIONS ASKED
Everthing you will receive is new in the box, the press and collator, I will only take the turret and the dies out of the box to set them up saving you time. Again if you would like to do this yourself or just dont want me to for whatever reasin feel free to let me know. Below is some information on the press from the manufaturer, feel free to ask me any questions at all. 

Thanks Matthew, please ask any questions you would like :)

Product Information
The Lee Pro 1000 Progressive Press is a great press for beginning reloaders or seasoned veterans. Just add a bullet and load a cartridge with each pull of the lever - all other operations are automatic. For added safety, primers and powder are fed only if a case is present. For fine adjustments or for experimenting, an alternate loading sequence allows for loading only one case at a time. Makes learning easy for the first time user. Turrets sold separately.
